{"source_key":"sha256-784c2f10bfe4a26d66c37ad545f72f01","record_index":31545,"record_hash":"sha256:70471954f336495bafef1c69259de47d33850e17d0b4bebc7360bfaef3bd82e4","timestamp":"2026-05-11T17:39:48.293Z","kind":"tool_result","source_event_kind":"codex:response_item:function_call_output","role":null,"text":"Chunk ID: d6c3ef\nWall time: 0.0000 seconds\nProcess exited with code 0\nOriginal token count: 1226\nOutput:\nJSON output can mirror that with a simple object. More detailed counters are\nuseful later, but not required for the first lifecycle POC.\n\n## GitMeta API Implication\n\nThe current high-level GitMeta APIs are close but not quite the right shape for\nagentlog-only sync:\n\n- `Session::serialize()` serializes all shareable metadata according to global\n  filter rules.\n- `Session::pull()` fetches and materializes configured metadata refs.\n- `Session::push_once()` pushes the main serialized metadata ref.\n\nUsing those directly would make `but agentlog sync` exchange unrelated metadata\ntoo. That breaks the command's scope.\n\nPrefer a small GitMeta API extension over reimplementing transport in\n`but-agentlog`. The API should let a caller exchange an explicit key scope.\nConceptually:\n\n```text\nserialize only keys matching:\n  gitbutler:agent-sessions\n  gitbutler:agent-session:**\n\nwrite local ref for that scope:\n  refs/meta/local/agentlog\n\nfetch/push the matching remote ref:\n  refs/meta/agentlog\n\nmaterialize only that fetched agentlog ref\n```\n\nThe GitMeta-owned scope can be modeled as `SyncScope`:\n\n```text\nname: agentlog\nlocal ref:  refs/meta/local/agentlog\nremote ref: refs/meta/agentlog\nmatches key:\n  key == \"gitbutler:agent-sessions\"\n  key starts with \"gitbutler:agent-session:\"\n```\n\nExact function names can be decided in `git-meta`, but the important API\nproperty is that key scope is command-scoped, not achieved by mutating the\nuser's persistent `meta:filter` or `meta:local:filter` configuration.\n\nThe API also needs scoped synchronization bookkeeping. GitMeta's incremental\nserialize/materialize state must be tracked per key scope or per serialized ref,\nnot with one global marker. Syncing only agentlog keys must not advance the\nstate used by default all-metadata serialization, and default serialization must\nnot make agentlog-only sync skip local agentlog changes.\n\nScoped materialization is also required. Materializing `r\n[TRUNCATED]\nnded non-fast-forward retry\n\nPrefer APIs that make this concrete use case easy to write correctly, then leave\nadditional routing, multiple scopes per command, custom merge policy, and extra\nreporting for later.\n\nKeep the implementation pragmatic and small. Less code is easier to understand,\ntest, and change while the feature is still early. Do not code-golf or obscure\nthe flow, but prefer direct functions, simple data structures, and focused tests\nover speculative extensibility.\n\nUse [Agentlog Maintainability Playbook](maintainability-playbook.md) at useful\n  sharing behavior for the POC.\n\n## Implementation Milestones\n\n1. Add `SyncScope` to `git-meta`.\n   - It should carry a name, local ref suffix/ref, remote ref suffix/ref, and a\n     key matcher.\n   - It should be general enough for non-GitButler callers.\n\n2. Add scoped sync bookkeeping in `git-meta`.\n   - Track serialization/materialization state per scope or per serialized ref.\n   - Keep the existing default/all-metadata lifecycle independent.\n\n3. Add scoped serialization in `git-meta`.\n   - Serialize only keys matched by the `SyncScope`.\n   - Write `refs/meta/local/<scope-name>` for the agentlog scope.\n   - Do not mutate persistent filter rules to achieve this.\n\n4. Add scoped materialization in `git-meta`.\n   - Materialize only keys matched by the `SyncScope`.\n   - Missing keys outside the scope must not affect local SQLite state.\n   - Missing remote ref means initial sync, not deletion.\n\n5. Add scoped push/fetch sync in `git-meta`.\n   - Fetch `refs/meta/<scope-name>` into its matching tracking ref when it\n     exists.\n   - Push `refs/meta/local/<scope-name>` to `refs/meta/<scope-name>`.\n   - Retry non-fast-forward with the boring fetch/materialize/serialize loop.\n\n6. Add `but agentlog sync` in GitButler.\n   - Define the agentlog `SyncScope` with the exact key matcher.\n   - Default `--remote` to `origin`.\n   - Keep output terse and privacy-aware.\n\n7. Add focused validation.\n   - GitMeta tests cover scoped bookkeeping, scoped materialization isolation,\n","tool_name":null,"tool_input":null,"source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-11T17:39:48.293Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"function_call_output","call_id":"[REDACTED:entropy]"}}}